title: Funny man Sean Hughes in Stafford tonight
text:
Throughout his life he has been battling to stay on the right side of sanity – and in middle age he has realised that the two sides of his brain are in constant conflict. What do you think? Be the first to comment 
There is common sense against mumbo jumbo and mumbo jumbo seems to have the upper hand. 
The show, which will feature tonight at Stafford’s Gatehouse, consists of stories including being serenaded at the break of dawn by Robert Smith. For more information on events in Staffordshire and the surrounding area click here . Receive daily email updates from the Express & Star
